        <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
        <p class="last-updated">Last Updated: February 7, 2025</p>
        
        <h2>1. Introduction</h2>
        <p>This privacy policy explains how our Einbürgerungstest Practice App handles your data. We are committed to protecting your privacy and being transparent about our practices.</p>
        
        <h2>2. Data Collection and Usage</h2>
        <p>Our app does NOT collect or transmit any personal data. All data, including:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Progress tracking</li>
            <li>Bookmarked questions</li>
            <li>Practice test results</li>
            <li>Settings preferences</li>
        </ul>
        <p>is stored locally on your device only and is never transmitted to our servers or any third parties.</p>
        
        <h2>3. Internet Permission</h2>
        <p>The app does not require or use internet access. All functionality works offline.</p>
        
        <h2>4. Third-Party Services</h2>
        <p>We do not integrate with any third-party services or analytics platforms.</p>
        
        <h2>5. Data Retention</h2>
        <p>All data is stored locally on your device and remains there until you uninstall the app or clear app data through your device settings.</p>
        
        <h2>6. Contact</h2>
        <p>For any privacy-related questions, please contact the email on the play store listing.</p>
